Steps to Reproduce:

``` cpp
monsterClip->stopAllActions();
monsterClip->setScale(0);  // (a)
Vector<FiniteTimeAction*> actions;
actions.pushBack(Spawn::createWithTwoActions(
        FadeIn::create(0.3f),
        EaseBackOut::create(ScaleTo::create(0.3f, 1.0f)))); // (b)
auto seqence = Sequence::create(actions);
monsterClip->runAction(seqence);
```

`monsterClip` is defined as `spine::SkeletonAnimation*`, and if you do change the code which marks like `(a)` with `monsterClip->setScale(1)` the monster would showed properly. Seems like the fragment (b) is always ignored if `setScale(0)`. In the same time I never used the code `removeAllActions` to stop code (b) 

If within  code (b) is remove `EaseBackOut` action around `ScaleTo` - spine draws perfect.

In the end, sometimes a code within ScaleTo is being crashed here:

``` cpp
void ScaleTo::update(float time)
{
    if (_target)
    {
        _target->setScaleX(_startScaleX + _deltaX * time);  // <--- HERE, says _target is already deleted
        _target->setScaleY(_startScaleY + _deltaY * time);
        _target->setScaleZ(_startScaleZ + _deltaZ * time);
    }
}
```

In cocos2d-x 3.10 this code has had worked perfectly

